                    <msContents>
                        <summary>This plate records the donation of part of the income of the pearl fisheries at Maṉṉār and Tūttukkuṭi to the temple in Āvuṭaiyārkōyil. The donor is allegedly Tirumalai Nāyakkar (r. 1623-1659), but the date on the plate (śaka 1461, A.D. 1539) does not correspond to the period of his reign.</summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p/>
                            
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
